tes who made Paris their home this summer.\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 845, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 3.905911854000164e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the last race and emotional goodbye, however, is an action-packed Saturday that will feature nine event finals and nine more chances for athletes to reach the podium in Paris.\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 3.905911854000164e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Saturday's schedule will kick off at 1 a.m. Eastern with the men's marathon and Eliud Kipchoge's quest to become the first athlete to win the event three times.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh, and at 39, he's also the two-time defending Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond that storyline is the fact that the marathon is one of the original events of the modern Olympics, which first were held in 1896.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:When Are The Marathons At The 2024 Paris Olympic Games: What To Know  Medals also will be awarded in the men's high jump, men's 800, women's javelin, women's 100-meter hurdles, men's 5,000, women's 1,500 and the prestigious 4x400 relays.\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Track and field fans already saw history made in the preliminary round of the men's 4x400 on Friday when16-year-old Quincy Wilson ran the opening leg for the United States, making him the youngest Olympian in Team USA history.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.9999920789136867, \"rank\": 5.82054030635591e-06, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"score\": 0.9748781966287583, \"rank\": 0.025703873960850155, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 1833, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9984963553350164, \"rank\": 0.0009590920695106627, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1884, \"end\": 1892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9999984630133428, \"rank\": 1.5369599792723023e-06, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wilson helped the men qualify for Saturday's final, and the wom